  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 5e28c2e20bb6c4240a55d8edffb777ec, type: 3}
  m_Name: Gaps
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NewDialogueData
  npcName: Chime
  dialogueLines:
  - LineID: Start
    Speaker: Chime
    text: I don't think that's enough...we need to help Derry run away.
    lineTone: 0
    NPCGender: 
    NextLineID: Part II
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices: []
    objectivesToActivate: []
  - LineID: Part II
    Speaker: Chime
    text: Hurry, we need to find a way to bridge those gaps! You have the ability
      to float, I should have mentioned it earlier. Press A when you're close to
      a gap to activate your ability, then press A whenever the indicator is in the
      green zone to stay in the air.
    lineTone: 0
    NPCGender: 
    NextLineID: Part III
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices: []
    objectivesToActivate: []
  - LineID: Part III
    Speaker: Chime
    text: I think you can use those crates to fill the gaps enough for Derry to make
      it across.
    lineTone: 0
    NPCGender: 
    NextLineID: 
    endDialogueAfterLine: 1
    choices: []
    objectivesToActivate:
    - guideDarryToSafety
